<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1163974284277">
<term>Doppler effect</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1163975431988">the apparent change in wavelength or frequency of the radiation from a source due to its relative motion away from or toward the observer</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1163974402475">
<term>radial velocity</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1163975371223">motion toward or away from the observer; the component of relative velocity that lies in the line of sight</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
